Shelbie Brooke Richards and Sarah Adelia Graves were sentenced to 8 years in prison for their role in the 2011 murder of James Craig Anderson . 
  Richards and Graves were part of a group of white teens who repeatedly searched for black men to assault in Jackson, Mississippi . 
  Anderson died after being beaten and run over by a truck in June 2011 . 
  Richards was sentenced to eight years and Graves was given 5 years for conspiracy to commit a hate crime . 
 